President Obama will host the White House Science Fair on October 18th, showcasing the winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) competitions. The event aims to inspire students to excel in these fields and emphasizes the importance of STEM education for the country's economic future. The fair fulfills a commitment made by the President in 2009 to recognize and celebrate the achievements of young individuals in science and innovation. The event will kick off a week-long celebration of science and engineering, with the USA Science and Engineering Festival taking place across the country.